    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26b.54a"/>
                
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>An Open Book, Cross, Candles, and Globe</figDesc>    
                </figure>
                
                <hi rend="caps">IN HOC SIGNO</hi>
                
                <lg>
                    <l>In troubled times again we hear</l>
                    <l>The angel chorus, sweet and clear</l>
                    <l>The angel chorus wending near</l>
                    <l>And we who try to feed His sheep</l>
                    <l>Have now a world-wide watch to keep</l>
                    <l>(The dispossessed, the young who weep)</l>
                    <l>Threatened starvation, West Berlin,</l>
                    <l>There we have Allies, kith and kin,</l>
                    <l>Only through us can hope to win</l>
                    <l>Starvation's threat. Christ comes again</l>
                    <l>This Yuletide in the hearts of men,</l>
                    <l>Thus peace on earth and only then.</l>
                </lg>
                
                Margarette Ball Dickson
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26b.54b"/>
                
                <opener><salute>Dear Dr <hi rend="caps">J.N.</hi>:</salute></opener> <p>Dr Coleman writes me you will be with us at <unclear>Oak Haven</unclear> again,Aug 19-22, am <hi rend="caps">VERY</hi> glad, The Wo<del>u</del><add>r</add>ld gretewt<sic>greatest</sic> e<del>i</del><add>p</add>ic poet! Hope you are well.Always i<unclear reason="missing">n</unclear> my prayers. Your lectures were some of the finest - ever h<del>r</del><add>e</add>ard and your personality,understanding, Li<del>-,</del><add>t-</add>Reputation and outlook ln<sic>in</sic> life. thanks for being you And best holiday wishes,God bless you and yours and your efforst<sic>efforts</sic>.</p> <closer><signed>Margarette Ball Dickson</signed></closer> 
                
                <postscript>
                    <p>My h<del>i</del><add>u</add>sband, Chris Jensen, the Dane sends regards</p>
                
                    <p>we saw Hamlets castle, Isanore and his grave.</p>
                </postscript>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    <del/><add><hi rend="caps">C.</hi></add> Jensen
                    Marg. Ball Dickson
                    209 - <hi rend="caps">E.N.</hi> Staples M<unclear/>
                </ab>
                
                <ab type="postmark">STAPLES, MINN DEC 21 530OM 1958</ab>
                
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>3 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>U.S. POSTAGE 3Â¢
                    IN GOD WE TRUST
                    LIBERTY</p>
                </figure>
                
